<emphasis id="D6E0C4185140182DFF0EF8FAEE531B39" bold="true" box="[151,363,1893,1918]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">FIGURES 356−363</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="239463895140182DFEE3F8F9ED551B39" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[378,621,1894,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abscondita" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185140182DFEE3F8F9ED551B39" box="[378,621,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Pygoluciola abscondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDD379635140182DFDEFF8F9EDD61B3A" box="[630,750,1894,1918]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185140182DFDEFF8F9EDDF1B39" bold="true" box="[630,743,1894,1918]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
males. (syntype series of males of 
<taxonomicName id="239463895140182DFBFDF8F9EA111B39" authorityName="E. Olivier" authorityYear="1891" box="[1124,1321,1894,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abscondita">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185140182DFBFDF8F9EA111B39" box="[1124,1321,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Luciola abscondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 356, 358 habitus dorsal; 357 habitus ventral (after soaking for an hour in soapy water); 359−361 aedeagus: 359 ventral; 360 dorsal; 361 right lateral (horizontal arrow indicates membranous apical area of LL; vertical arrow indicates sausage shaped lobe of LL); 362 aedeagal sheath apex of sheath sternite only; 363 abdomen dorsal. Scale lines are 1 mm.
