<subSubSection id="AC8E4B815147182AFF5EFE0AEB541E78" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E42B180A5147182AFF5EFE0AEB541E78" blockId="124.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFF5EFE0AEE0C1DE8" bold="true" box="[199,308,405,431]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Remarks</emphasis>
. Olivier described the elytra as black and considered this species close to 
<taxonomicName id="239463895147182AFBE7FE09EBC61DE8" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1888" box="[1150,1278,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticeps">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFBE7FE09EBC61DE8" box="[1150,1278,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">L. hirticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but without a median dark pronotal marking. It is difficult to determine the precise pronotal colour which may be due to retraction of the underlying fat body. 
<taxonomicName id="239463895147182AFD99FE41EDA01DB0" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" box="[512,664,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abscondita" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFD99FE41EDA01DB0" box="[512,664,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">P. abscondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDD379635147182AFD39FE42EC1B1DB0" box="[672,803,477,503]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFD39FE42EC241DB0" bold="true" box="[672,796,477,503]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is one of two species presently assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="239463895147182AFA8CFE42EAA41DB0" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[1301,1436,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFA8CFE42EAA41DB0" box="[1301,1436,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where the aedeagal and sheath morphology are suggestive of the related genus 
<taxonomicName id="239463895147182AFB92FD9EEBB11E5C" authorityName="Ballantyne Lambkin &amp; Fu" authorityYear="2013" box="[1035,1161,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Abscondita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFB92FD9EEBB11E5C" box="[1035,1161,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Abscondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and where the sheath is terminated by a boomerang shaped section. The other species is 
<taxonomicName id="239463895147182AFCFEFDB9ECDD1E78" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[871,997,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFCFEFDB9ECDD1E78" box="[871,997,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">P. insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D6E0C4185147182AFC75FDBAEB541E78" bold="true" box="[1004,1132,549,575]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDD379635147182AFC75FDBAEB541E78" box="[1004,1132,549,575]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
